Get sleep hours for a single day

const getSleepHours = day => {
  day = day.toLowerCase();
  switch (day) {
    case 'monday': return 8;
    case 'tuesday': return 7;
    case 'wednesday': return 6;
    case 'thursday': return 8;
    case 'friday': return 5;
    case 'saturday': return 9;
    case 'sunday': return 7;
    default: return 'Error: Invalid day';
  }
};


Returns the hours of sleep for each day.

Handles invalid input.

Calculate total actual sleep

const getActualSleepHours = () =>
  getSleepHours('monday') +
  getSleepHours('tuesday') +
  getSleepHours('wednesday') +
  getSleepHours('thursday') +
  getSleepHours('friday') +
  getSleepHours('saturday') +
  getSleepHours('sunday');


Adds up all the daily hours to get total weekly sleep.

Set ideal sleep hours

const getIdealSleepHours = idealHours => idealHours * 7;


Multiplies your ideal nightly sleep by 7 for a week.

Calculate sleep debt

const calculateSleepDebt = () => {
  const actualSleepHours = getActualSleepHours();
  const idealSleepHours = getIdealSleepHours(8);

  if (actualSleepHours === idealSleepHours) {
    console.log(`Perfect! You got exactly the right amount of sleep: ${actualSleepHours} hours.`);
  } else if (actualSleepHours > idealSleepHours) {
    console.log(`You got more sleep than needed. You slept ${actualSleepHours - idealSleepHours} hours extra.`);
  } else {
    console.log(`You need more rest. You slept ${idealSleepHours - actualSleepHours} hours less than ideal.`);
  }
};


Compares actual sleep vs ideal sleep and logs a friendly message.

ðŸ’¡ Optional Improvements

Use an object instead of switch

const sleepHours = {
  monday: 8,
  tuesday: 7,
  wednesday: 6,
  thursday: 8,
  friday: 5,
  saturday: 9,
  sunday: 7
};

const getSleepHours = day => sleepHours[day.toLowerCase()] || 0;


Cleaner, easier to update, and avoids the long switch statement.

Flexible ideal sleep

You could prompt the user for their ideal hours:

const idealHours = parseInt(prompt("Enter your ideal nightly sleep hours:"), 10);


Return sleep debt instead of only console.log

Makes the function reusable in other parts of a program:

return actualSleepHours - idealSleepHours;
